      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>6 threads, <a href=item.html?item=10427&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f102379948616711>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=item.html?item=10427&mid=102379948616711>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=item.html?item=10427&mid=102379948616711>Who and how</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=10427&mid=102379948616711#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, Jun 11th 8:52 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=162349><span id= >Tiburones</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This sword drops from the grimling prince,&nbsp;&nbsp;Garzemort.  Be careful, his corpse poofs very quickly after he dies.  I learned this the hard way.  He can be found in the Vah Shir outpost after the grimlings control the three main camps in Hollowshade.  the prince stays rooted to one spot, but his bodyguards roam and repop quickly.  <br><br>Ending the war is simple, but a little tedious.  Wait for a species to go on &quot;offense&quot; against another species, assist them in killing the unique camp guardians, once a species takes another camp, they begin spawning all over that camp, then simply wait for the same species to attempt a raid on the last remaining camp, assist them, then run to the outpost to find their prince.<br><br>This quest can be done fairly easily by a 40+ healer/melee combo, or by a solo 50-ish kiter, nothing exceedingly dangerous here, other than the bodyguards, which can be avoided if you are careful.<br><br>A note about the defenders, they summon, so be sure you have enough firepower to destroy them without the help of the attackers (who will con indifferent to you).  Another thing about them, I am still not certain of this, but it seemed like whenever the sonic wolves killed an attacking grimling, the grimling then became a fresh new sonic defender.  This is purely anecdotal, but I think that is what happened, although it was hard to tell with the constant disorientation from the summoning,  Again, I learned this the hard way.  Best to kill the defenders before the attacking side arrives, then they can simply march in uncontested and claim the camp.  It takes a while for the &quot;correct&quot; side to attack sometimes, just be patient, read the messages, and enjoy your new items.  <br><br>Good luck, hope that helps.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Jun 11 08:48:36 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br>Tiburones De San José<br>Overlord of Tunare's Benevolence<br>Zebuxoruk</td></td></tr>
